hat can give a specific result, nobody can make one experience that=\r\n result, no matter what ritual one does. However, even great souls have a l=\r\not of negative karmas in their optional pool and even evil people have a lo=\r\nt of positive karmas in their optional pool, and hence powerful remedies, c=\r\nurses and blessings can often make some difference.\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; =C3=83=E2=80=9A=\r\n=C3=82=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; This point is well illustrated by the &quot;Guru Charitra&quot; st=\r\nory Digamber ji referred in his point (3).\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; =C3=83=E2=80=9A=C3=82=C2=\r\n=A0\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; *=C3=83=E2=80=9A=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=83=E2=80=9A=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=83=E2=\r\n=80=9A=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=83=E2=80=9A=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=83=E2=80=9A=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=\r\n=83=E2=80=9A=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=83=E2=80=9A=C3=82=C2=A0 *=C3=83=E2=80=9A=C3=82=\r\n=C2=A0=C3=83=E2=80=9A=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=83=E2=80=9A=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=83=E2=80=9A=\r\n=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=83=E2=80=9A=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=83=E2=80=9A=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=83=E2=\r\n=80=9A=C3=82=C2=A0 *\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; =C3=83=E2=80=9A=C3=82=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; If one thinks =\r\nthat one can escape the fruits of one&#39;s actions, one is mistakened. God is =\r\nnot like us human beings, who may show favoritism towards those who praise =\r\nthem or bribe them. The He-aspect of God is a witness to the play of action=\r\ns and fruits. The She-aspect of God is the power that impartially and impas=\r\nsionately manages the fine balance and order within this play of actions an=\r\nd fruits. All beings are equal in Her eyes, from the lowest of evil persons=\r\n to the noblest of saints. She administers just and balanced delivery of fr=\r\nuits to actions using available agents.\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; =C3=83=E2=80=9A=C3=82=C2=A0\n&gt;=\r\n&gt; &gt;&gt; The karmas we committed in the past are already in the pipeline and wi=\r\nll give their results sooner or later. The best we can do with them, with s=\r\nome effort, is to perhaps reorder them somewhat. The mos